            "answer_text": "For this answer, I studied the art of sleep science. Not really\u2026but Kinda.  First of all, how long does it take you to fall asleep? It differs by person but it takes the average person about fourteen minutes to fall asleep. According to the web, if you want to you want to wake up at 8:00 am, you should fall sleep at: 11:00 PM or 12:30 AM or 2:00 AM or 3:30 AM However, you must take into account the time it takes you to fall asleep, so you should begin trying to sleep at: 10:45 PM or 12:15 AM or 1:45 AM or 3:15 AM * If you want to you want to wake up at 6:00 am, you should fall sleep at: 9:00 PM or 10:30 AM or 12:00 AM or 1:30 AM However, you must take into account the time it takes you to fall asleep, so you should begin trying to sleep at: 8:45 PM or 10:15 AM or 11:45 AM or 1:15 AM * I\u2019m sure you probably get the jist of it\u2026. so I hope this helped.  Hypnic Jerk = Pain Sleep well people. ",
